Masters (MS) in Civil Engineering in USA: Best Universities, Eligibility, Courses, Scholarship, Jobs

  • 270 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Jun 10,2023 12:49 PM IST

Civil Engineering is one of the most sought-after career option to pursue and studying Masters in civil engineering from USA offers numerous benefits to international students. Are you interested in becoming a future civil engineer? Read further to know in detail information on MS in Civil Engineering in USA.

As a civil engineer aspirant, achieving a Masters (MS) in Civil Engineering in USA is a major step towards building a successful career. The United States hosts some of the world's top ranked universities offering advanced programs and research opportunities in the field of civil engineering.  Planning to pursue your Masters in Civil Engineering in USA? Read to know the importance of a Masters in Civil Engineering in USA, the best universities for this degree, eligibility criteria, popular courses, scholarships, and job prospects of Civil Engineering.

MS in Civil Engineering

Masters (MS) in Civil Engineering helps students gain knowledge and skills required to solve complex engineering problems. Students of these programs are highly sought after in various industries such as construction, transportation, environmental, and urban planning. Have a look at the highlights of MS in civil engineering in USA.

DegreeMaster of Science (MS) in Civil Engineering
Course Duration9 months- 2 years
SpecializationsConstruction Management, Civil and Environmental Engineering, Architecture, Structural Engineering, Geotechnical Engineering, Water Resources Engineering
Eligibility
Bachelor’s in Civil Engineering
Exams RequiredGRE, IELTS or TOEFL
Minimum GRE Requirement155 in verbal and quantitative
4.0 in analytical writing

Why study Masters (MS) in Civil Engineering in USA?

Masters in Civil Engineering in USA offers various benefits to students to excel in their careers. Here are the main reasons to pursue MS in Civil Engineering in USA.

  • The education system of US is based on modern teaching methods which emphasizes more on practical skills along with the theoretical knowledge.
  • Access to a global network of professionals, experts, and alumni is provided which can open up a multitude of career opportunities.
  • American Universities offer a welcoming multicultural environment to international students.

Eligibility Requirements for MS in Civil Engineering in USA

Students have to meet the following admission requirements to study Masters degree in Civil engineering in USA.

  • Bachelor's degree in civil engineering or a related field
  • A minimum GPA of 3.0 on a scale of 4.0
  • Proof of English language proficiency (IELTS or TOEFL)
  • GRE scores
  • Letters of recommendation
  • Statement of purpose
  • CV/ Resume

Applying for MS in Civil Engineering without GRE

The Graduate Record Examination commonly known as GRE is a standardized test that is required by many universities for the admission process in USA. However, there are some universities which offer MS in Civil Engineering program without the GRE score requirement and evaluates student’s profile based on academic record, work experience and other factors.

Job Prospects for Civil Engineering graduates

Civil engineers are in high demand across various industries such as construction, transportation, environmental, and urban planning.
Below are some of the most popular job roles for Civil Engineering in USA.

Design Engineer: Design engineers develop and analyse engineering designs and solutions for various projects like buildings, bridges, and transportation systems.

Construction Manager: Construction managers oversee the planning, budgeting, and execution of construction projects.

Environmental Engineer: Environmental engineers design and implement systems to protect the environment and public health, including water and wastewater treatment systems, air pollution control systems and more.

Transportation Engineer: Transportation engineers design and analyse transportation systems, including highways, bridges, and airports

Structural Engineer: Structural engineers are responsible for designing structural systems that include buildings and bridges ensuring that they are safe and stable.

Pursuing a Masters in civil engineering in the USA can be a rewarding and fulfilling experience for students interested in this field. With world-renowned universities, diverse courses, and several scholarships available, students can choose from plenty of options. Are you planning to pursue MS in Civil Engineering in USA? FAQ

Is studying MS in Civil Engineering in USA worth it?
The United States is known for its world class education in top ranked universities. Various specializations are offered for Master’s degree in civil engineering and students can choose according to their interests and passion.
Which documents are required to apply for admission in universities of USA?
•    Academic Transcripts and Certificates
•    English Language Proficiency Test Scores (IELTS, TOEFL, PTE)
•     GRE Scorecard
•    Statement of Purpose (SOP)
•    Curriculum Vitae (CV)/ Resume
•    2-3 Letters of Recommendation (LOR’s)
Is it compulsory to submit GRE score for admission?
Many universities have a requirement of GRE score but there are universities which don’t require GRE score for the admission process.
Which are the top universities to pursue MS in Civil Engineering in USA?
University of Massachusetts, University of the Pacific, University of Illinois, Washington State University and California State University are the top universities to study MS in Civil Engineering.
What are the other job roles after MS in Civil Engineering in USA?
Civil Engineer
Water Resource Engineer
Project Engineer
Construction Project Manager
Field Engineer
Geotechnical Engineer
